This paper involves the use of deep learning architectures for image classification, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper focuses on the application of these architectures in medical imaging for glaucoma severity grading, which could also fall under the medical imaging (cs.MED) sub-category. The use of deep learning for image classification also falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves the use of pre-processing techniques for generating regions of interest, which could also fall under the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
